## Service Version Detection

### Basic Version Detection (`-sV`)
```bash
nmap -sV 10.10.10.10
```

**What it does:**
- Connects to open ports
- Sends probes to identify service
- Determines software name and version

**Example output:**
```
PORT    STATE SERVICE  VERSION
22/tcp  open  ssh      OpenSSH 8.2p1 Ubuntu
80/tcp  open  http     Apache httpd 2.4.41
443/tcp open  ssl/http nginx 1.18.0
```

**Why it matters:**
- Identifies vulnerable versions
- Helps research exploits
- Maps software inventory
- Essential for vulnerability assessments

---

### Aggressive Version Detection (`-A`)
```bash
nmap -A 10.10.10.10
```

**Enables:**
- Version detection (`-sV`)
- OS detection (`-O`)
- Script scanning (`-sC`)
- Traceroute (`--traceroute`)

**Warning:** Very noisy and easily detected!

