## Output Formats

### Normal Output (`-oN`)
```bash
nmap -oN scan_results.txt 10.10.10.10
```
- Human-readable format
- Same as terminal output
- Good for reports

---

### XML Output (`-oX`)
```bash
nmap -oX scan_results.xml 10.10.10.10
```
- Machine-readable format
- Can be imported into other tools
- Best for automation

---

### Grepable Output (`-oG`)
```bash
nmap -oG scan_results.gnmap 10.10.10.10
```
- Easy to parse with grep/awk
- One line per host
- Good for scripting

---

### All Formats (`-oA`)
```bash
nmap -oA scan_results 10.10.10.10
```
- Saves in all three formats:
  - scan_results.nmap (normal)
  - scan_results.xml (XML)
  - scan_results.gnmap (grepable)

