## Practical Examples

### Quick Network Survey
```bash
# Find live hosts
nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24

# Scan live hosts for common ports
nmap 192.168.1.1-254
```

---

### Web Server Enumeration
```bash
# Find web servers and their versions
nmap -p 80,443,8080,8443 -sV 10.10.10.0/24
```

---

### Full Host Assessment
```bash
# Comprehensive scan with version detection
sudo nmap -sS -sV -p- -T4 -oA full_scan 10.10.10.10
```
- SYN scan (`-sS`)
- Version detection (`-sV`)
- All ports (`-p-`)
- Aggressive timing (`-T4`)
- Save all formats (`-oA`)

---

### Stealth Scan
```bash
# Slow, stealthy scan
sudo nmap -sS -T2 -f -D RND:10 10.10.10.10
```
- SYN scan (`-sS`)
- Polite timing (`-T2`)
- Fragment packets (`-f`)
- Decoy scan with 10 random IPs (`-D RND:10`)

